      "id": "mem-MEMORY-key-lessons",
      "content": "### Face Winding Order (Critical)\nThree.js `FrontSide` culling requires CCW vertex winding when viewed from outside.\nIndex pattern `0,1,2, 2,3,0` means corners must be listed CCW from the viewer's perspective.\nGot this wrong initially → half the block faces were invisible.\n\n### GameState Initialization\nDon't initialize `GameState.current` to a value if you plan to `transition()` to it on start.\n`transition()` has an early return `if (newState === current)` which silently skips the event emit.\nFi",
      "summary": "Key Lessons",
